  "text": "Finally, it is also noteworthy that the Weibull distribution, which is traditionally used in wind modelling in the Caribbean, performed poorly for both datasets using all the metrics investigated. This is likely due to the large amount of low to zero wind speed measurements. Castellanos [CITATION_1] has also noted that the Weibull distribution performs poorly when the data contains a large proportion of low wind speeds (Figs. 19, 20 ; Table 12 ).",
